title: The Honor System - Rise and Run (2003) {Out of Print} [FLAC]
description:
Out of print Grey Flight Records release.

I almost released their complete discography.  It turns out Solidarity Records released a "Collection" CD which includes Demo Tape, Single File (Asian Man Records), and 100% Synthetic albums (Double Zero Records).
You can buy a copy here: <a href="
http://www.solidarityrecordings.com/products/7227-the-honor-system-collection-cd" rel="nofollow" target="_NEW">
http://www.solidarityrecordings.com/products/7227-the-honor-system-collection-cd</a>
Should their "Collection" release go out-of-print, I do have the original albums on FLAC and will release them.

This is one of many CDs I ripped for posterity a while back.
I went through many phases when it came to rip/encode/split methods.
This one was made before I documented the split.
I used CUETools to verify each file and generate an AccurateRip/CTDB log. This log as well as the original EAC log is included.

I'm new to this.  Please comment and tell me if I'm doing anything right or wrong.  Thanks!
